Sprint Objectives with "Good", "Better", and "Best" Scenarios
Sprint 2 Goal

Ensure seamless integration of modules with a robust backoffice, planning, and GDPR compliance while advancing 3D visualization and business continuity capabilities.
Scenarios of Success
1. Good (Minimum Viable Success)

    Objective: Deliver critical features that allow core functionality across modules, ensuring usability and compliance with foundational requirements.
    Results Expected:
        Integrated UI with role-based menu adjustments.
        Basic Backoffice functionality for patients and admin user management.
        Planning module generates a good schedule using heuristics.
        Basic deployment and risk management in the business continuity module.
        Foundational GDPR analysis and a prototype breach notification system.
    User Stories Covered:
        Integration: 6.1.1, 6.1.2
        Backoffice: 6.2.1, 6.2.4, 6.2.9, 6.2.14
        Planning Module: 6.3.1, 6.3.3
        Business Continuity: 6.4.1, 6.4.4
        GDPR: 6.6.1, 6.6.2
        3D Visualization: Not prioritized in Good scenario.

2. Better (Target Success)

    Objective: Deliver planned functionality with improved synchronization, usability, and visualization while maintaining compliance and stability.
    Results Expected:
        Integrated UI synchronizes with real-time scheduling data.
        Comprehensive Backoffice features for patient and admin management, including profile editing and operation requisitions.
        Planning module generates both optimal and heuristic-based schedules within reasonable timeframes.
        Advanced deployment automation and access control in the business continuity module.
        Expanded GDPR compliance and breach management system.
        Basic 3D visualization with interactive controls and lighting.
    User Stories Covered:
        Integration: 6.1.1–6.1.4
        Backoffice: 6.2.1–6.2.17
        Planning Module: 6.3.1–6.3.3
        Business Continuity: 6.4.1–6.4.6
        GDPR: 6.6.1, 6.6.2
        3D Visualization: 6.5.1, 6.5.2, 6.5.4

3. Best (Exceeding Expectations)

    Objective: Deliver all planned features with enhancements, ensuring optimal performance, advanced visualization, and full compliance.
    Results Expected:
        Fully integrated UI with real-time synchronization across modules, including operation and room availability.
        Complete Backoffice functionality with advanced search and GDPR-compliant data management.
        Planning module generates efficient schedules for large datasets using optimized algorithms.
        Fully automated business continuity processes with advanced risk quantification and reporting.
        Comprehensive GDPR compliance with automated breach detection, reporting, and response.
        Advanced 3D visualization with realistic textures, ambient lighting, and fully functional camera controls.
    User Stories Covered:
        Integration: 6.1.1–6.1.5
        Backoffice: 6.2.1–6.2.21
        Planning Module: 6.3.1–6.3.3
        Business Continuity: 6.4.1–6.4.8
        GDPR: 6.6.1, 6.6.2
        3D Visualization: 6.5.1–6.5.4
